Etymology[edit]

From sub +‎ petō.

Pronunciation[edit]

  • (Classical) IPA(key): /ˈsup.pe.toː/, [ˈsʊp.pɛ.t̪oː]
  • (Ecclesiastical) IPA(key): /ˈsup.pe.to/, [ˈsup.pɛ.t̪ɔ]

Verb[edit]

subpetō (present infinitive subpetere, perfect active subpetīvī or subpetiī, supine subpetītum); third conjugation

  1. Alternative form of suppetō
